  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-66d88e0c-7fff-1ac4-f8d9-f15ab3eb1fd0&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.26;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed rear dormer, by reason of its size, would be overly dominant within the rear roof slope, to the detriment of the character and appearance of the host building and the area. As such the proposal is contrary to policies D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) of the London Plan 2021, policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP3 of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the recommendations of the Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Extensions and Alterations 2009.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;"
